27/09/2009
NEW YORK, United States -- UN Secretary General Ban Ki-moon said on Friday (September 25th) that he has full confidence in the activities of Matthew Nimetz, mediator in the name dispute between Greece and Macedonia. 
At a meeting in New York with Macedonian President Gjorge Ivanov on the sidelines the 64th session of the UN General Assembly, Ban indicated that the organisation has excellent co-operation with Macedonia. 
He also expressed hope that the dispute will be settled soon, and voiced his support for Macedonia's EU and NATO integration efforts. 
(Inpress, Vecer, MINA, Makfax, MIA - 26/09/09)
